### Health check
GET http://localhost:3000/api/health
Accept: application/json

###

### Get all events
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events
Accept: application/json

###

### Get today's events (server date or pass query date)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events/today
Accept: application/json

###

# Example: override today's date (useful when testing)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events/today?date=2025-11-16
Accept: application/json

###

### Search events by date or category or search term
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events?date=2025-11-16
Accept: application/json

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/events?category=Music
Accept: application/json

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/events?search=Yoga
Accept: application/json

###

### Get single event by id
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Create event (admin)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Event",
  "date": "2025-12-20",
  "startTime": "10:00",
  "endTime": "12:00",
  "location": "Test Hall",
  "category": "Test",
  "description": "A test event",
  "capacity": 10
}

###

### Update event
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/events/22
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Morning Yoga",
  "capacity": 25
}

###

### Delete event
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/events/22

###

### Register for an event
POST http://localhost:3000/api/registrations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": 1,
  "fullName": "Test Person",
  "email": "test.person@example.com"
}

###

### Get registrations for an event
GET http://localhost:3000/api/registrations/event/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Get registrations for a user by email (URL encode email)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/registrations/user/ben.t%40example.com
Accept: application/json
